<br>
So I need to know from someone who has actually done it, can it be tri-quested?  If so, how did you do it, try to be as detailed as possible.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
<br>
Azzalar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 7:43:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need definitive answer: Tri-questing</span><hr size=1> It should be possible.  Just make sure the Wizard getting the staff is the last to turn in his staff. <p><BR>
