<br>
Very possible, it's how I got mine. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
First and most important, make sure you(the epic receiver) do *ALL* the +Truespirit steps.<br>
<br>
Here is how I personally did, I will make generic names to make it easier to understand.<br>
<br>
This is the situation, and I was the epic receiver.<br>
<br>
Me-Gabstik+note<br>
Person1-BCS<br>
Person2-Gnarled<br>
<br>
Now, I made sure to do all the +truespirit steps.  I was apprehensive for the whole quest till the very end with Solomen.<br>
<br>
Here is what we did.<br>
<br>
1. I instruct the others about how it works, make sure they are VERY clear on what to do.  (following is what to do) Also, MAKE SURE YOU HAVE A GENERAL INVENTORY SLOT OPEN FOR THE BAG.<br>
<br>
2. I hand in the 'Note to Arantir' to Dargon, which spawns Arantir.<br>
<br>
3. I hail Arantir, he asks for the 3 staves.<br>
<br>
4. Person1 and Person2 BOTH put the staffs in trade window but DO NOT hit trade.<br>
<br>
5. I invs Person1 and Person2.<br>
<br>
6. Person1 hands in BCS, AS SOON as he hands it he says, 'IN'.<br>
<br>
7. AS SOON as Person2 sees Person1 say, 'IN' he hands his Gnarled in and says, 'IN' as soon as it is in.<br>
<br>
8. AS SOON as I see Person2 say, 'IN' I hand in my Gabstik staff.<br>
<br>
9. Rejoice as you now have the bag to take Solomen. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Good luck, it's pretty easy, just make sure to have a general invo. slot open for the bag, and do not let anyone hail Arantir during this except for yourself for that *1* time, someone else hailing him in the middle of it can SERIOUSLY mess it all up.<br>
<br>
Oh, and early congrats on your epic! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
